Arsenal boss, Mikel Arteta, has sent a clear message to Tottenham Hotspur following their Premier League 2-1 win over West Ham on Sunday. Arsenal defeated West Ham at the London Stadium, thanks to two goals from Rob Holding and Gabriel, while Tottenham won 3-1 against Leicester City. Asked whether the race for the top four between Arsenal and Tottenham could go all the way till the end of the season, Arteta said the pressure is there for both teams. “Let’s see. Another seven days to prepare for the match,” Arteta told BBC Sport. “The pressure is there and we both won, so let’s go.” Arteta’s side will clash with Tottenham on May 12 after their next game against Leeds United on May 8. Arsenal are currently in the fourth position on the log with two points ahead of Tottenham (5th position) after 34 matches.